This paper deals with the problem of inductive matrix completion, which involves predicting ratings for new users/movies based on side information such as age or genre. This is a problem that falls under the umbrella of machine learning and data analysis, and is closely related to topics such as low-rank matrix estimation and multi-label regression. Therefore, the most likely sub-category for this paper is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper also deals with optimization and information theory, which suggests that cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are also possible sub-categories.
